text: The year 2009 is the seventh year in the history of Jungle Fight, a mixed martial arts promotion based in Brazil. In 2009 Jungle Fight held 5 events beginning with, Jungle Fight 12: Warriors 2. ==Events list== {| class="sortable wikitable succession-box" style="font-size:90%;" |- ! scope="col" | # ! scope="col" | Event Title ! scope="col" | Date ! scope="col" | Arena ! scope="col" | Location |- | align=center| 16 | Jungle Fight 16 | | Maracanãzinho Gymnasium | Rio de Janeiro, Brazil |- | align=center| 15 | Jungle Fight 15 | | Pacaembu Gymnasium | São Paulo, Brazil |- | align=center| 14 | Jungle Fight 14: Ceará | | Paulo Sarasate Gymnasium | Fortaleza, Brazil |- | align=center| 13 | Jungle Fight 13: Qualifying Fortaleza | | Fighter Sport Academy | Fortaleza, Brazil |- | align=center| 12 | Jungle Fight 12: Warriors 2 | | Team Nogueira Training Center | Rio de Janeiro, Brazil |} ==Jungle Fight 12: Warriors 2== Jungle Fight 12: Warriors 2 was an event held on March 21, 2009 at The Team Nogueira Training Center in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. ===Results=== ==Jungle Fight 13: Qualifying Fortaleza== Jungle Fight 13: Qualifying Fortaleza was an event held on March 28, 2009 at The Fighter Sport Academy in Fortaleza, Brazil. ===Results=== ==Jungle Fight 14: Ceará== Jungle Fight 14: Ceará was an event held on May 9, 2009 at The Paulo Sarasate Gymnasium in Fortaleza, Brazil. ===Results=== ==Jungle Fight 15== Jungle Fight 15 was an event held on September 19, 2009 at The Pacaembu Gymnasium in São Paulo, Brazil. ===Results=== ==Jungle Fight 16== Jungle Fight 16 was an event held on October 17, 2009 at The Maracanãzinho Gymnasium in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. ===Results=== == See also == * Jungle Fight ==References== Category:2009 in mixed martial arts Category:Jungle Fight events
